  <div class="content">
    I am trying to write a custom action that will set the visible property of a
    <var>TStatusBar</var> on and off. I assigned this action to a menu item and
    when I select this menu item at runtime the status bar is hidden. The
    problem is that the menu item (connected to the action) is disabled, so I
    can't view the statusbar again. I think that it's a matter of how the
    <var>TMenuActionLink</var> behaves (the action controls the
    <var>Enabled</var> property of the menu). I tried to set the
    <var>Enabled</var> property in the action to true, but no avail. The menu is
    still disabled. Is there any way to do this?
  </div>
</div>

